S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
A N A C T
RELATING TO GENERAL ASSEMBLY -- COMMITTEES AND STAFF
Introduced By: Representatives Serpa, Ackerman, Fellela, Read, Chippendale, Edwards,
O'Brien, Baginski, J. Brien, and Azzinaro
Date Introduced: February 12, 2025
Referred To: House State Government & Elections
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 22-6-15 of the General Laws in Chapter 22-6 entitled "Committees
2 and Staff" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 22-6-15. Annual appropriations.
4 The general assembly shall annually appropriate a sum that shall be necessary to carry out
5 the provisions of §§ 22-6-10 — 22-6-14 and § 22-6-16.
6 SECTION 2. Chapter 22-6 of the General Laws entitled "Committees and Staff" is hereby
7 amended by adding thereto the following section:
8 22-6-16. Nonprofit funding transparency.
9 Any nonprofit entity, as a condition to requesting state grants or funding from the general
10 assembly, shall submit to the general assembly and post on their website, a complete and detailed
11 list consisting of the ten (10) highest paid director, officer and employee salaries, costs, benefits
12 including, but not limited to, health insurance and rental cars, and any and all forms of
13 compensation provided to those individuals in the organization. Any other sources of funding,
14 including fundraising, endowments, trusts, memorial giving and/or any and all activities that fund
15 the nonprofit entity shall also be included in the disclosure.
16 SECTION 3. This act shall take effect upon passage.
